---
description: Task runner workflow for CkSoccer
alwaysApply: true
---

This project uses docs/tasks.md as the execution source of truth.

Required task workflow:
1. Read docs/tasks.md before implementation work.
2. Find the first task with Status: in_progress.
3. If no task is in_progress, find the first task with Status: pending.
4. Execute only one major task unless explicitly told to continue.
5. Stay within the selected task scope.
6. Do not silently pull work from future tasks.

Task update rules:
- When starting a pending task, change its status to in_progress.
- When a task is fully completed, change its status to done.
- Only mark a task done if all Definition of done items are actually satisfied.
- If work is partial, keep the task in_progress.
- If blocked, mark it blocked and add a short blocker note under the task.
- After marking a task done, set the next eligible pending major task to in_progress.
- Never leave more than one major task in_progress at the same time.

Task discipline:
- Respect:
  - Goal
  - Why
  - Scope
  - Do not change
  - Affected files
  - Definition of done
  - Manual tests
- If the task is underspecified, choose the smallest professional implementation that satisfies it.
- If the requested work reveals missing prerequisite work, stop and document the issue rather than improvising a huge refactor.

Response discipline after implementation:
- State which task was executed.
- List changed files.
- List manual tests to run.
- State whether the task was marked done, kept in_progress, or marked blocked.